CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, November 5, 1955, pg. 1B reads: "The Prime Minister tells newspapermen how you deal with the British. Left to right: Joseph Shuman, Post-Gazette; Beverly Carter, Dr. Azikiwe; Charles Pierson, The Press, and Edward Becker, the Sun-Telegraph."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Joseph Shuman, Beverly Carter, Eastern Nigerian Prime Minister Nnamdi Azikiwe, Charles Pierson, and Edward Becker, posed in interior with vertical blinds on windows
